text: {{Infobox settlement | name = Racha-Lechkhumi and Kvemo Svaneti | native_name = რაჭა-ლეჩხუმი და ქვემო სვანეთი | native_name_lang = ka | settlement_type = Mkhare (region) | image_map = Racha-Lechkhumi in Georgia (disputed hatched).svg | map_caption = | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = | seat = Ambrolauri | parts_type = Municipalities | parts_style = para | parts = | p1 = 4 | leader_title = Governor | leader_name = Archil Japaridze | area_total_km2 = 4990 | population_total = 32089 | population_as_of = 2014 census | population_density_km2 = auto |timezone = Georgian Time |utc_offset = +4 |timezone_DST = |utc_offset_DST = | iso_code = GE-RL }} Racha-Lechkhumi and Kvemo Svaneti is a region in Georgia. The capital city is Ambrolauri. Part of the region is controlled by South Ossetia. Besides Ambrolauri, the region includes the municipalities of Lentekhi, Oni, and Tsageri. The region has the historical provinces of Racha, Lechkhumi and Kvemo Svaneti. Category:South Ossetia Category:Regions of Georgia (country)
